{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Manufacturing Yield Analysis Example\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the data-scientist plugin workflow on a synthetic manufacturing dataset.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Business question**: Which process parameters drive yield? Are there confounded variables?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Dataset**: 200 production runs with temperature, pressure, humidity, operator, shift, material batch, and yield %."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": ,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add ds_skill to path\n",
    "repo_root = Path.cwd().parents[1]\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, str(repo_root / \"plugins/data-scientist/skills/analysis-workflow/scripts\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "from ds_skill import readiness, correlation, regression\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load and profile the data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv('yield_data.csv')\n",
    "df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Shape: {df.shape}\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Data readiness check\n",
    "\n",
    "Use the `readiness` module to score the dataset across 8 dimensions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "readiness_result = readiness.score_readiness(df)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Overall score: {readiness_result.overall_score}/8\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nDimension scores:\")\n",
    "for dim, score in readiness_result.dimension_scores.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"  {dim}: {score}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if readiness_result.blockers:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n⚠️ Blockers: {readiness_result.blockers}\")\n",
    "if readiness_result.warnings:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n⚠️ Warnings: {readiness_result.warnings}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Correlation analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Find which variables correlate with yield."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "numeric_cols = ['temperature_c', 'pressure_psi', 'humidity_pct', 'defect_count', 'yield_pct']\n",
    "corr_result = correlation.pairwise_correlation(\n",
    "    df[numeric_cols],\n",
    "    method='pearson',\n",
    "    fdr_correction=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filter for yield correlations\n",
    "yield_corrs = [\n",
    "    (pair['var1'], pair['var2'], pair['correlation'], pair['p_value'])\n",
    "    for pair in corr_result.pairs\n",
    "    if 'yield_pct' in (pair['var1'], pair['var2'])\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Correlations with yield_pct:\")\n",
    "for v1, v2, r, p in sorted(yield_corrs, key=lambda x: abs(x[2]), reverse=True):\n",
    "    other = v1 if v2 == 'yield_pct' else v2\n",
    "    sig = '***' if p < 0.001 else '**' if p < 0.01 else '*' if p < 0.05 else ''\n",
    "    print(f\"  {other:20s}: r={r:6.3f}, p={p:.4f} {sig}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Visualize key relationships"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(12, 10))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Temperature vs yield (expect quadratic)\n",
    "axes[0, 0].scatter(df['temperature_c'], df['yield_pct'], alpha=0.6)\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('Temperature (°C)')\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Yield %')\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_title('Temperature vs Yield')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Pressure vs yield (expect linear)\n",
    "axes[0, 1].scatter(df['pressure_psi'], df['yield_pct'], alpha=0.6)\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_xlabel('Pressure (PSI)')\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Yield %')\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_title('Pressure vs Yield')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Operator (confounded with shift)\n",
    "df.boxplot(column='yield_pct', by='operator', ax=axes[1, 0])\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_xlabel('Operator')\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_ylabel('Yield %')\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_title('Yield by Operator')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Shift\n",
    "df.boxplot(column='yield_pct', by='shift', ax=axes[1, 1])\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_xlabel('Shift')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_ylabel('Yield %')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_title('Yield by Shift')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Regression analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Build a model to quantify driver effects."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Prepare features (add temperature squared to capture quadratic)\n",
    "X = df[['temperature_c', 'pressure_psi', 'humidity_pct']].copy()\n",
    "X['temperature_c_sq'] = X['temperature_c'] ** 2\n",
    "y = df['yield_pct']\n",
    "\n",
    "reg_result = regression.linear_regression(X, y, diagnostics=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"R² = {reg_result.r_squared:.3f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Adjusted R² = {reg_result.adj_r_squared:.3f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nCoefficients:\")\n",
    "for coef in reg_result.coefficients:\n",
    "    sig = '***' if coef['p_value'] < 0.001 else '**' if coef['p_value'] < 0.01 else '*' if coef['p_value'] < 0.05 else ''\n",
    "    print(f\"  {coef['feature']:20s}: {coef['coefficient']:7.3f} (p={coef['p_value']:.4f}) {sig}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if reg_result.diagnostics:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nDiagnostics:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Durbin-Watson: {reg_result.diagnostics.get('durbin_watson', 'N/A')}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Condition number: {reg_result.diagnostics.get('condition_number', 'N/A')}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Check for confounding\n",
    "\n",
    "Operator C appears better, but is it confounded with shift?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Crosstab operator × shift\n",
    "ct = pd.crosstab(df['operator'], df['shift'], margins=True)\n",
    "print(\"Operator × Shift crosstab:\")\n",
    "print(ct)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mean yield by operator × shift\n",
    "print(\"\\nMean yield by operator × shift:\")\n",
    "print(df.groupby(['operator', 'shift'])['yield_pct'].agg(['mean', 'count']).round(2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "**Confirmed drivers**:\n",
    "- Temperature (quadratic effect — optimal around 350°C)\n",
    "- Pressure (linear positive effect)\n",
    "- Humidity (weak positive effect)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Confounded**:\n",
    "- Operator C works mostly night shift, making it hard to separate their effects\n",
    "\n",
    "**Recommendation**:\n",
    "- Run a designed experiment (DOE) with balanced operator × shift to deconfound\n",
    "- Target temperature 350°C ± 5°C, pressure 105-110 PSI"
   ]
  }
 ],
